description.p:
Accordingly, in a first aspect, the invention provides control means for a stairlift, said stairlift including:
a stairlift rail having rail sections which, when installed, are arranged at different angles to a horizontal plane;
a carriage mounted on said rail for movement there-along;
a chair pivotally mounted on said carriage;
over-speed braking means operable to brake said carriage with respect to said rail;
speed sensing means operable to sense the speed of said carriage along said rail; and
angle sensing means operable to sense positions of said chair at which the angle thereof varies with respect to said horizontal plane,
said control means being operable to receive a signal from said speed sensing means and to generate a command to operate said over-speed braking means when a carriage speed in excess of a pre-determined speed is sensed, said control means being characterized in that it is further operable to receive a signal from said angle sensing means and to generate a command to operate said over-speed braking means when said angle sensing means senses that the angle of said chair with respect to said horizontal plane is at or in excess of a predetermined limit.

In a second aspect the invention provides a method of controlling the operation of a stairlift, said stairlift including:
a stairlift rail having rail sections which, when installed, arc arranged at different angles to a horizontal plane;
a carriage mounted on said rail for movement there-along;
a chair pivotally mounted on said carriage;
over-speed braking means operable to brake said carriage with respect to said rail;
speed sensing means operable to sense the speed of said carriage along said rail; and
angle sensing means operable to sense positions of said chair at which the angle thereof varies with respect to said horizontal plane,
said method including receiving a signal from said speed sensing means and causing said over-speed braking means to operate when the speed of said carriage exceeds a predetermined speed, said method being characterized in that it further includes receiving a signal from said angle sensing means and causing said over-speed braking means to operate if the angle of said chair with respect to said horizontal plane is at or in excess of a predetermined limit.

claim.claim-text:
Control means for a stairlift (10), said stairlift including:
a stairlift rail (13) having rail sections which, when installed, are arranged at different angles to a horizontal plane;
a carriage (12) mounted on said rail (13) for movement there-along;
a chair (11) pivotally mounted on said carriage;
over-speed braking means (21, 30) operable to brake said carriage (12) with respect to said rail (13);
speed sensing means operable to sense the speed of said carriage (12) along said rail (13); and
angle sensing means (22) operate to sense positions of said chair at which the angle thereof varies with respect to said horizontal plane,
said control means being operable to receive a signal from said speed sensing means and to generate a command to operate said over-speed braking means (21, 30) when a carriage speed in excess of a pre-determined speed is sensed, said control means being characterized in that it is further operable to receive a signal from said angle sensing means (22) and to generate a command to operate said over-speed braking means (21, 30) when said angle sensing means senses that the angle of said chair with respect to said horizontal plane is at or in excess of a predetermined limit.

A method of controlling the operation of a stairlift (10), said stairlift including:
a stairlift rail (13) having rail sections which, when installed, are arranged at different angles to a horizontal plane;
a carriage (12) mounted on said rail (13) for movement there-along;
a chair (11) pivotally mounted on said carriage (12);
over-speed braking means (21, 30) operable to brake said carriage (12) with respect to said rail (13);
speed sensing means operable to sense the speed of said carriage (12) along said rail (13); and
angle sensing means (22) operable to sense positions of said chair (11) at which the angle thereof varies with respect to said horizontal plane,
said method including receiving a signal from said speed sensing means and causing said over-speed braking means (21, 30) to operate when the speed of said carriage (12) exceeds a predetermined speed, said method being characterized in that it further includes receiving a signal from said angle sensing means (22) and causing said over-speed braking means (21, 30) to operate if the angle of said chair (11) with respect to said horizontal plane is at or in excess of a predetermined limit.

Moyen de commande pour un monte-escalier (10), ledit monte-escalier comportant :
un rail (13) de monte-escalier comprenant des tronçons de rail qui, une fois installés, sont agencés en formant des angles différents par rapport à un plan horizontal ;
un chariot (12) monté sur ledit rail (13) pour effectuer un mouvement le long de celui-ci ;
une chaise (11) montée pivotante sur ledit chariot ;
un moyen de freinage en survitesse (21, 30) servant à freiner ledit chariot (12) par rapport audit rail (13) ;
un moyen de détection de vitesse servant à détecter la vitesse dudit chariot (12) le long dudit rail (13) ; et
un moyen de détection d'angle (22) servant à détecter des positions de ladite chaise auxquelles son angle varie par rapport audit plan horizontal,
ledit moyen de commande servant à recevoir un signal en provenance du moyen de détection de vitesse et à générer une commande pour mettre en fonctionnement ledit moyen de freinage en survitesse (21, 30) lorsqu'une vitesse du chariot dépassant une vitesse prédéfinie est détectée, ledit moyen de commande étant caractérisé en ce qu'il sert en outre à recevoir un signal en provenance dudit moyen de détection d'angle (22) et à générer une commande pour mettre en fonctionnement ledit moyen de freinage en survitesse (21, 30) lorsque ledit moyen de détection d'angle détecte que l'angle de ladite chaise par rapport audit plan horizontal atteint ou dépasse une limite prédéfinie.

Procédé de commande du fonctionnement d'un monte-escalier (10), ledit monte-escalier comportant :
un rail (13) de monte-escalier comprenant des tronçons de rail qui, une fois installés, sont agencés en formant des angles différents par rapport à un plan horizontal ;
un chariot (12) monté sur ledit rail (13) pour effectuer un mouvement le long de celui-ci ;
une chaise (11) montée pivotante sur ledit chariot (12) ;
un moyen de freinage en survitesse (21, 30) servant à freiner ledit chariot (12) par rapport audit rail (13) ;
un moyen de détection de vitesse servant détecter la vitesse dudit chariot (12) le long dudit rail (13) ; et
un moyen de détection d'angle (22) servant à détecter des positions de ladite chaise (11) auxquelles son angle varie par rapport audit plan horizontal,
ledit procédé consistant à recevoir un signal en provenance du moyen de détection de vitesse et à mettre en fonctionnement ledit moyen de freinage en survitesse (21, 30) lorsque la vitesse dudit chariot (12) dépasse une vitesse prédéfinie, ledit procédé étant caractérisé en ce qu'il consiste en outre à recevoir un signal en provenance dudit moyen de détection d'angle (22) et à mettre en fonctionnement ledit moyen de freinage en survitesse (21, 30) si l'angle de ladite chaise (11) par rapport audit plan horizontal atteint ou dépasse une limite prédéfinie.
